"<p>A unital homomorphism between rings R and S is a ring homomorphism that sends the identity element of R to the identity element of S.</p>\n\n<p>Homomorphisms (between objects in any algebraic category like groups, rings, vector spaces, etc.) preserve the algebraic structure, and if you want a map between rings with an identity element, it is natural to require this to preserve this element (since it satisfies unique properties).</p>\n"	""	""	"2010-07-21T13:28:39.320"	""	""	""	"1"	"2"	"9"	""	"2010-07-21T13:28:39.320"	""	"330"	""	""	""	""	"324"	""
