"<p>Isaac's <a href=""http://math.stackexchange.com/questions/438/1-is-not-1-so-where-is-the-mistake/439#439"">answer</a> is correct, but it can be hard to see if you don't have a strong knowledge of your laws. These problems are generally easy to solve if you examine it line by line and simplify both sides.</p>\n\n<p>$$\\begin{align*}\r\n\\sqrt{-1} &amp;= \\hat\\imath &amp;\r\n\\mathrm{LHS}&amp;=i, \\mathrm{RHS}=i\r\n\\\\\r\n1/\\sqrt{-1} &amp;= 1/\\hat\\imath &amp;\r\n\\mathrm{LHS}&amp;=1/i=-i, \\mathrm{RHS}=-i\r\n\\\\\r\n\\sqrt{1}/\\sqrt{-1} &amp;= 1/\\hat\\imath &amp;\r\n\\mathrm{LHS}&amp;=1/i=-i, \\mathrm{RHS}=-i\r\n\\\\\r\n\\textstyle\\sqrt{1/-1} &amp;= 1/\\hat\\imath &amp;\r\n\\mathrm{LHS}&amp;=\\sqrt{-1}=i, \\mathrm{RHS}=-i\r\n\\end{align*}$$</p>\n\n<p>We can then see that the error must be assuming $\\textstyle\\sqrt{1}/\\sqrt{-1}=\\sqrt{1/-1}$.</p>\n"	""	""	"2011-07-04T03:24:33.553"	"2"	""	""	"5"	"2"	"123"	""	"2010-07-22T13:19:27.403"	""	"482"	"1208"	""	"2011-07-04T03:24:33.553"	""	"438"	""
